data.description: Wouldn't you love a $25 a month electric bill? Welcome home to 959 Toledo Bend in the highly desired Midtown Reserve. With new solar panels on this energy efficient home, the average monthly electric bill this year has been $20-25 per month - even in the 100-degree weather! This home is immaculate. An inviting kitchen and dining space with views to the front yard and walkway feature several large windows, stainless steel appliances (refrigerator included), creamy subway tile backsplash, and granite countertops. The spacious family room is in the center of the home and has ample lighting and bright windows with a door to the covered back patio. Primary bedroom is generous and bathed in natural lighting. The en-suite showcases a separate tub and shower, double sinks, closeted toilet and walk-in closet. Entertaining space is extended to the outdoor covered patio with two large paved additions - the perfect space to enjoy a beautiful Texas sunset! Storage building on a slab will remain. Midtown Reserve is a master planned community with access to extensive walking trails including Lick Creek Park. Nearby shopping (including the brand new Costco), restaurants and hospitals make this neighborhood convenient for everything you need.
